We are an expat football team in Stockholm with two 11-a-side teams. One team is in Stockholm Division 6 and one plays in the 11-a-side Korpen league.

Our squad is around 25-30 guys mostly between 25-35 and from all over, including UK, France, Spain, Germany and Sweden.

As well as playing football, we enjoy socialising together and enjoying a football discussion over a beer in the pub.

Get in touch to come and join a training session to meet the lads and have a kickabout!

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

description:
Hello and welcome to Stockholms largest Field Hockey Club, Mesaicos.se

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IZCzbslH8jo

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Cycling trips,

â€¢ mainly in Denmark and neighbouring countries (Scandinavia and Baltics)

â€¢ in small groups (2-5 persons, maybe more for shorter trips)

â€¢ of 1 to 10 days duration at moderate speed (15-20 km/hour, 60-80 km/day)

â€¢ staying at reasonably cheap hotels, airbnb or youth hostels.

I have launched this meetup on my own, but encourage you to show initiative and use this as a forum where you are most welcome to launch your own projects and spread information about relevant events.

You need not have a fully-fledged detailed plan in order to launch a project - this can be done later together with those meetup members that show interest.

You are free to post anything, at least until further notice. However, what I see as the specific for this meetup, compared to other cycling meetups, is that it is not about sport, but rather about leisure, nature, having a good time and seeing interesting places, especially such that are off the beaten road, but need not be far away - as an example I am preparing a plan for a cycling trip to the Russian enclave Kaliningrad.

I find it very useful to combine cycling trips with train transport - e.g. to cycle to Berlin and take the train back to Copenhagen, - in general it is very easy to bring a bicycle with you on the train in those European countries I have tried (Denmark, Germany, France, Belgium, Luxembourg).

Poul Andersen
name: Cycling tourism in Europe

description:
OK, so you may watch English Premier League games on TV in pubs in central CPH already. But it's hit-or-miss how often you get to sit with someone who, a) wants to speak English, or b) has something vaguely intelligent to say about the game. This group will provide both. You probably support Arsenal, Chelsea, Liverpool, Man City or Utd, or even Tottenham (teams listed strictly in alphabetical order!). But you love the drama of all the big games, and you might come along even when your team isn't playing, providing the crack is good. Oh, and with the price of beer in CPH, you're probably happy just to buy your own. Me? I can make one pint last a whole game.

P.S. Have you seen there a sister facebook group where we run events?

If you want to make sure you won`t miss a game, join:https://www.facebook.com/groups/148825532442638

However, what I see as the specific for this meetup, compared to other cycling meetups, is that it is not about sport, but rather about leisure, nature, having a good time and seeing interesting places, especially such that are off the beaten road, but need not be far away - as an example I am preparing a plan for a cycling trip to the Russian enclave Kaliningrad.

I find it very useful to combine cycling trips with train transport - e.g. to cycle to Berlin and take the train back to Copenhagen, - in general it is very easy to bring a bicycle with you on the train in those European countries I have tried (Denmark, Germany, France, Belgium, Luxembourg).

Poul Andersen

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

description:
Hello and welcome to Stockholms largest Field Hockey Club, Mesaicos.se

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IZCzbslH8jo

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

We are an expat football team in Stockholm with two 11-a-side teams. One team is in Stockholm Division 6 and one plays in the 11-a-side Korpen league.

Our squad is around 25-30 guys mostly between 25-35 and from all over, including UK, France, Spain, Germany and Sweden.

As well as playing football, we enjoy socialising together and enjoying a football discussion over a beer in the pub.

Get in touch to come and join a training session to meet the lads and have a kickabout!

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

description:
Hello and welcome to Stockholms largest Field Hockey Club, Mesaicos.se

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IZCzbslH8jo

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

We look forward to meeting you soon.

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Cycling trips,

â€¢ mainly in Denmark and neighbouring countries (Scandinavia and Baltics)

â€¢ in small groups (2-5 persons, maybe more for shorter trips)

â€¢ of 1 to 10 days duration at moderate speed (15-20 km/hour, 60-80 km/day)

â€¢ staying at reasonably cheap hotels, airbnb or youth hostels.

I have launched this meetup on my own, but encourage you to show initiative and use this as a forum where you are most welcome to launch your own projects and spread information about relevant events.

You need not have a fully-fledged detailed plan in order to launch a project - this can be done later together with those meetup members that show interest.

You are free to post anything, at least until further notice. However, what I see as the specific for this meetup, compared to other cycling meetups, is that it is not about sport, but rather about leisure, nature, having a good time and seeing interesting places, especially such that are off the beaten road, but need not be far away - as an example I am preparing a plan for a cycling trip to the Russian enclave Kaliningrad.

I find it very useful to combine cycling trips with train transport - e.g. to cycle to Berlin and take the train back to Copenhagen, - in general it is very easy to bring a bicycle with you on the train in those European countries I have tried (Denmark, Germany, France, Belgium, Luxembourg).

Poul Andersen
name: Cycling tourism in Europe

description:
OK, so you may watch English Premier League games on TV in pubs in central CPH already. But it's hit-or-miss how often you get to sit with someone who, a) wants to speak English, or b) has something vaguely intelligent to say about the game. This group will provide both. You probably support Arsenal, Chelsea, Liverpool, Man City or Utd, or even Tottenham (teams listed strictly in alphabetical order!). But you love the drama of all the big games, and you might come along even when your team isn't playing, providing the crack is good. Oh, and with the price of beer in CPH, you're probably happy just to buy your own. Me? I can make one pint last a whole game.

P.S. Have you seen there a sister facebook group where we run events?

- The Meetup Group organizer will book courts and provide shuttlecocks

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.

And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

We look forward to meeting you soon.

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Cycling trips,

â€¢ mainly in Denmark and neighbouring countries (Scandinavia and Baltics)

â€¢ in small groups (2-5 persons, maybe more for shorter trips)

â€¢ of 1 to 10 days duration at moderate speed (15-20 km/hour, 60-80 km/day)

â€¢ staying at reasonably cheap hotels, airbnb or youth hostels.

I have launched this meetup on my own, but encourage you to show initiative and use this as a forum where you are most welcome to launch your own projects and spread information about relevant events.

You need not have a fully-fledged detailed plan in order to launch a project - this can be done later together with those meetup members that show interest.

You are free to post anything, at least until further notice. However, what I see as the specific for this meetup, compared to other cycling meetups, is that it is not about sport, but rather about leisure, nature, having a good time and seeing interesting places, especially such that are off the beaten road, but need not be far away - as an example I am preparing a plan for a cycling trip to the Russian enclave Kaliningrad.

I find it very useful to combine cycling trips with train transport - e.g. to cycle to Berlin and take the train back to Copenhagen, - in general it is very easy to bring a bicycle with you on the train in those European countries I have tried (Denmark, Germany, France, Belgium, Luxembourg).

Poul Andersen

description:
OK, so you may watch English Premier League games on TV in pubs in central CPH already. But it's hit-or-miss how often you get to sit with someone who, a) wants to speak English, or b) has something vaguely intelligent to say about the game. This group will provide both. You probably support Arsenal, Chelsea, Liverpool, Man City or Utd, or even Tottenham (teams listed strictly in alphabetical order!). But you love the drama of all the big games, and you might come along even when your team isn't playing, providing the crack is good. Oh, and with the price of beer in CPH, you're probably happy just to buy your own. Me? I can make one pint last a whole game.

P.S. Have you seen there a sister facebook group where we run events?

Come and join us, let us build a fun and healthy community together.

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IZCzbslH8jo

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Sharon

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IZCzbslH8jo

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

As well as playing football, we enjoy socialising together and enjoying a football discussion over a beer in the pub.

Get in touch to come and join a training session to meet the lads and have a kickabout!

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Welcome to the wonderful world of Pickleball.

A social, active and addictive sport that we are delighted to bring to Sweden. <br>

It's a cross between badminton, table tennis and tennis and is played either indoors or out. It's for all ages and experience levels. My aunt has just started playing and she's 65 so don't go thinking your not fit enough or fast enough, this is truly a sport for all.

The mission of The Swedish Pickleball Association is to create a fun and social atmosphere where we can laugh, get healthy and learn more about this unique sport. <br>

We play weekly and want to grow the team. Everyone is welcome.

We have paddles and balls for all so get involved and find out what the heck we are raving about!

Make sure you like us on Facebook too as we'll update with videos and events.

For a little introduction please see :-

The rise and rise of Pickleball <br>

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2KNhIgOkXM <br>

The basic rules

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLWj2LXecHU

Look forward to seeing you soon. Sharon & Kim

If you want to get involved you can also email at sharon@imagineif.io

<br>

<br>

description:
7 or 8 -a-side football friendlies in Stockholm. Indoors 5-a-side in the freezing winter. You know the drill.

Games are open to all ages, genders, languages etc...

Basic football skills are expected. Common sense (showing up on time, playing the full game, etc) is also expected :)

As this is a face-to-face group, your profile must have your real name and a photo that shows your face (no sunglasses, no cats, no dogs, no other animals... ) to get approved. This is so we recognise each other and avoid confusion in the attending/ waiting lists (happened before!)

See you then!

I run The Mesaicos Veterans Club for players over 35 years of age. We are a friendly, enthusiastic club with a vision to grow and compete in competitions and we're recruiting new members. We will start practising again after the summer in Sept.
It doesn't matter whether you've played before or have never picked up a stick we'll provide with all the help and support you need.
For more information about us here is the link to our Facebook page too. https://www.facebook.com/groups/389651148080749/


And if you need an introduction to how to play the game here's a little introduction.

We look forward to meeting you soon.

Sharon

category.name: sports/recreation
description:
Cycling trips,

â€¢ mainly in Denmark and neighbouring countries (Scandinavia and Baltics)

â€¢ in small groups (2-5 persons, maybe more for shorter trips)

â€¢ of 1 to 10 days duration at moderate speed (15-20 km/hour, 60-80 km/day)

â€¢ staying at reasonably cheap hotels, airbnb or youth hostels.

I have launched this meetup on my own, but encourage you to show initiative and use this as a forum where you are most welcome to launch your own projects and spread information about relevant events.

You need not have a fully-fledged detailed plan in order to launch a project - this can be done later together with those meetup members that show interest.

You are free to post anything, at least until further notice. However, what I see as the specific for this meetup, compared to other cycling meetups, is that it is not about sport, but rather about leisure, nature, having a good time and seeing interesting places, especially such that are off the beaten road, but need not be far away - as an example I am preparing a plan for a cycling trip to the Russian enclave Kaliningrad.

I find it very useful to combine cycling trips with train transport - e.g. to cycle to Berlin and take the train back to Copenhagen, - in general it is very easy to bring a bicycle with you on the train in those European countries I have tried (Denmark, Germany, France, Belgium, Luxembourg).

Poul Andersen
name: Cycling tourism in Europe

description:
OK, so you may watch English Premier League games on TV in pubs in central CPH already. But it's hit-or-miss how often you get to sit with someone who, a) wants to speak English, or b) has something vaguely intelligent to say about the game. This group will provide both. You probably support Arsenal, Chelsea, Liverpool, Man City or Utd, or even Tottenham (teams listed strictly in alphabetical order!). But you love the drama of all the big games, and you might come along even when your team isn't playing, providing the crack is good. Oh, and with the price of beer in CPH, you're probably happy just to buy your own. Me? I can make one pint last a whole game.

P.S. Have you seen there a sister facebook group where we run events?
